      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "<a id=\"_Toc492473622\">H 14939</a> – Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hammaad Bin Usman, who has narrated the following:",
          "<span class=\"first-chapter-phrase\"><span class=\"first-in-chapter character-a\">A</span>bu Abdullah</span><sup>asws</sup> has said: ‘The earth folds up during the end of the night’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "492. A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Khalid, from Usman Bin Isa, from Abu Ayyub Al-Khazaz who said: We intended to go out, so we went to greet Abu Abdullah (a.s.). So he (a.s.) said: ‘It is as if you all are seeking blessings for Monday’. So we said, ‘Yes’. So he (a.s.) said: ‘So which day is greater in evil than the day of Monday, the day in which our Prophet (saww) departed, and the Revelation was Raised (stopped) from us (a.s.). Do not go out, and go out on the day of Wednesday’."
        ]
      }
    }
